Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.07,0:25:37.55,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,985)}Theory: Harvesting the bontan fruit is also called bontan hunting
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.07,0:25:46.62,TLNote,,0,0,0,,{\pos(45,36)}TL note: As well as being a fruit 'bontan' is a word used \Nfor puffy pants, associated with 1980s high school delinquents. \N\NBontan hunting is the practice of hunting down those wearing \Nthem and robbing them of them; mainly associated with high school manga.\N\N Also, hunting and harvesting are the same word in Japanese
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.55,0:25:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(99,828)}So we checked the sightseeing website \Nof somewhere known for producing bontans,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.85,0:25:44.39,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,{\pos(542,1001)}Kagoshima-ken's Akune city
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.88,0:25:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(102,529)}And found it
