Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.05,0:30:26.39,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}(Kame) No, it was a cockroach! Don't they\N say if you've got one there's a hundred?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.39,0:30:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(507,894)}In that case I know how to get rid of it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.39,0:30:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(345,1018)}Seriously? Tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.39,0:30:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(685,898)}A spider will eat it for you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.39,0:30:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(435,1018)}A spider?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.73,0:30:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(711,898)}One as big as an iPad...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.73,0:30:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(435,1018)}An iPad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.40,0:30:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,898)}That's huge isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.40,0:30:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(675,1018)}Yep, and covered in thick hair
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.23,0:30:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(345,898)}Hey, that's scary
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.23,0:30:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(765,1018)}Dripping
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.30,0:30:43.24,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,That's the Wet iPad Tarantula!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.24,0:30:46.58,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,898)}(Kame) It's the most dangerous one
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.24,0:30:46.58,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}(Murasato) Just leave it in the room for 10 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.58,0:30:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(315,1018)}(Kame) Just forget it.\NI'm fine with the cockroach
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.08,0:30:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,898)}What do you do with the spider?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.08,0:30:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(345,1018)}It rustles in the ceiling doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.00,0:30:54.83,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Hey, get back on topic
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.83,0:30:57.75,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}(Kame) I'll have just swapped a cockroach for a tarantula
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.75,0:31:00.20,DefaultAqua,,0,0,0,,{\pos(838,380)}He's thinking about how\Nmuch he's imitating him
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.82,0:31:04.19,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,As he's subjected to successive hits of Nobu-style tsukkomi,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.20,0:31:08.20,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,Kimu has a suspicious expression
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.20,0:31:10.70,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.70,0:31:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(315,898)}Hey that's long
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.70,0:31:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(495,1018)}Yep and about as thick as me
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.37,0:31:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(315,898)}It's huge
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.37,0:31:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(645,1018)}And it's known for its pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.04,0:31:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(435,898)}Pattern?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.04,0:31:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(585,1018)}Yep, its whole body is paisley
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.56,0:31:20.82,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,No, a snake's too individualistic
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.82,0:31:25.30,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,{\fs85}No, a snake's too individualistic
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.11,0:31:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(345,838)}(Kame) Isn't that the Paisley Snake?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.38,0:31:30.22,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,After some tsukommi that seems like\Nit was somehow left out of a Chidori performance...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.22,0:31:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(355,658)}We're done.\NThank you very much
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.22,0:31:34.22,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}They finish their performance here
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.22,0:31:37.97,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,Will he warn them as expected, or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.76,0:31:42.73,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,You like Nobu, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.75,0:31:47.17,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Would I say I like him? I suppose
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.17,0:31:51.02,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,We're from the same area so...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.18,0:31:51.02,COverlay text 2,,0,0,0,,Ah, really? It felt like Hiroshima-ben
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.04,0:31:53.44,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,I think I might seem a bit like him
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.44,0:31:56.18,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Hmmm
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.18,0:31:59.65,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,But what about doing tsukommi with your fist clenched?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.31,0:32:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(285,898)}(Kame) Ah, yes
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.80,0:32:01.60,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Well.. . like...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.62,0:32:07.24,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Nobu does that too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.77,0:32:07.24,COverlay text 2,,0,0,0,,Yes, I suppose so
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.24,0:32:09.99,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Staff) So you're saying he's a bit like him?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.99,0:32:15.20,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,I looked at where he was from and was like "Ah Hiroshima". I have friends who are like that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.20,0:32:17.23,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,'That's just how it is' I thought
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.23,0:32:18.55,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Many people are like that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.57,0:32:21.07,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Like how people say 'what the hell' in Osaka-ben
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.07,0:32:25.66,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,If you've always spoken like that then there's no helping it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.22,0:32:25.66,COverlay text 2,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is how I usually speak
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.71,0:32:31.71,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,Surprisingly it appears he wasn't that \Nbothered about him speaking like Nobu
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.83,0:32:33.92,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}However...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.09,0:32:38.02,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,How is it being called "Mamaland"?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.02,0:32:40.99,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,There's a "Laland" already. Doesn't it bother you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.26,0:32:44.26,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Um, it does. There's Mamatarte-san too
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.26,0:32:47.93,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,I think it's good to have some flexibility
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.04,0:32:52.55,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,He's very sensitive to their being named similarly to other groups
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.57,0:32:55.24,CDefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}Yes, that was our last one
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.24,0:32:57.24,DefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,1018)}Matsumoto-san\Nhow was the last one?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.24,0:33:00.54,DefaultYellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(565,1018)}As we expected,\NKimu...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.76,0:33:04.46,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,wanted to throw a plastic bottle, just how Kinoshita does it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.41,0:33:06.62,DefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,898)}He's not that scary
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.41,0:33:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(745,1018)}He's not like that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.18,0:33:11.19,DefaultYellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(345,898)}He wanted to hit him in the eye with it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.18,0:33:11.19,DefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(405,1018)}No no...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.19,0:33:14.26,DefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,898)}He wouldn't go that far
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.19,0:33:14.26,DefaultYellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(375,1018)}So he's mellowed out
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.26,0:33:16.86,DefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,1018)}He instructed us too\Nwhen we were at NSC
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.86,0:33:19.93,DefaultAqua,,0,0,0,,{\pos(525,898)}Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.86,0:33:19.93,DefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,1018)}We were able to meet him then
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.93,0:33:22.70,DefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(345,898)}and he was fairly scary then
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.93,0:33:22.70,DefaultYellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(625,1018)}Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.70,0:33:25.70,DefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,1018)}He's been very kind\Nsince we graduated though
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.70,0:33:29.37,DefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,898)}Karen-chan, what did you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.70,0:33:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(285,1018)}One really made an impression with me
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.37,0:33:32.21,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,838)}the Bontan one
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.21,0:33:35.04,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,838)}I really loved it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.05,0:33:35.49,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Theory: Harvesting the bontan fruit is also called bontan hunting
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.04,0:33:38.38,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,838)}There's so many words like \Nthat in Japanese, aren't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.38,0:33:41.05,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}So I'd love for you to keep doing it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.05,0:33:45.89,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}And explaining something complicated\Nwith pictures was really helpful
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.89,0:33:51.27,CDefaultYellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}By the way, do you know the reason\Nwhy the students are pulling the bontans off?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.39,0:33:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,778)}Ah, umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.27,0:33:52.24,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,I don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.73,0:33:54.40,CDefaultYellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,778)}You didn't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.40,0:33:56.90,CDefaultYellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,778)}But you laughed so much
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.88,0:33:58.01,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,You didn't know but were able to enjoy it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.23,0:34:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,1018)}She really enjoyed it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.40,0:34:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,298)}Next it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.96,0:34:08.41,CDefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}Yes, here are Everyone's Theories \Nthat I chose
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.49,0:34:20.24,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,Theory: If you ask someone who definitely looks over 80\Nhow old they are and they reply 'I'm 60', you'll still answer 'you don't look it!'
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.69,0:34:24.19,DefaultAqua,,0,0,0,,{\pos(825,898)}I see
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.69,0:34:24.19,DefaultYellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(675,1018)}That's right
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.54,0:34:27.84,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,You can't say 'you look old'
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.03,0:34:28.03,DefaultAqua,,0,0,0,,{\pos(735,658)}Well, that's right
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.03,0:34:28.03,DefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(345,778)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.03,0:34:33.45,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,So we investigated if they'll still say the usual phrase 'you don't look it'
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.19,0:34:49.43,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,Theory: If you ask someone who definitely looks over 80\Nhow old they are and they reply 'I'm 60', you'll still answer 'you don't look it!'
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.71,0:34:51.71,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}And so...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.34,0:34:57.72,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1135,308)}He's in the same clothes
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.71,0:34:54.38,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}Thank you! Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.38,0:34:56.88,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,778)}It's Panther's Ogata! Hello
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.94,0:35:03.28,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,We've made a fake show where he interviews older people on the street to discover their health secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.28,0:35:10.59,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,We send in this 89-year old grandpa\Nwho couldn't possibly be 60
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.73,0:35:13.73,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}Let's see what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.60,0:35:16.83,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,How old are you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.83,0:35:18.07,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,I'm sixty
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.06,0:35:20.43,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Si... Sixty?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.06,0:35:20.43,COverlay text 2,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.44,0:35:24.14,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Ah... but... you're young, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.51,0:35:28.01,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}Taken by surprise,\Nall Ogata can say is...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.30,0:35:31.01,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,{\pos(363,810)}'you're young, aren't you?'
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.01,0:35:36.51,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,Then Ogata worries what he'll look like in his 50s if this man is 60
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.85,0:35:39.05,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,You're 60?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.75,0:35:39.05,COverlay text 2,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.36,0:35:41.42,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.35,0:35:41.42,COverlay text 2,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.42,0:35:44.83,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,So do you ever get told you look older than you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.83,0:35:45.80,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,I'm told that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.80,0:35:47.73,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,You are, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.73,0:35:50.97,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Is this on purpose...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.97,0:35:57.01,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,That's a sweater someone who's over 60 would wear, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.53,0:35:55.23,COverlay text 2,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,878)}Do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.01,0:35:59.74,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Is it not on purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.56,0:36:04.56,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1195,308)}He's still going!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.77,0:35:59.74,COverlay text 2,,0,0,0,,It's nothing like that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.08,0:36:01.11,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.48,0:36:04.85,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,\h\h\h\h\hIf you're 60 then...\h\h\h\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.85,0:36:07.42,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Taka-san, Ishibashi Takaaki-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.72,0:36:10.92,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,I was born in 1961
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.92,0:36:13.42,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,So compared to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.42,0:36:17.36,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,You're 16 years my senior
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.36,0:36:21.10,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Ah, 16 years... Ah, I see
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.10,0:36:24.26,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Huh, so that means you're the same age as Tunnels-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.29,0:36:24.26,COverlay text 2,,0,0,0,,That's right
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.57,0:36:28.67,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Wow
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.01,0:36:32.34,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Well I guess comedians are young
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.41,0:36:37.47,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,So he did not say "you don't look it"
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.48,0:36:39.48,DefaultAqua,,0,0,0,,{\pos(615,1018)}He was so persistent
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.48,0:36:43.49,CDefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}Yes, Ogata-kun didn't say it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.49,0:36:47.42,DefaultYellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(315,1018)}I thought it'd be fine since 'you don't look it' can mean something else
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.42,0:36:50.43,DefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(435,898)}Well, that's right
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.42,0:36:50.43,DefaultYellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,1018)}But he just said 'you're young'
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.43,0:36:53.43,CDefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}Yes, because he clearly wasn't 60
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.43,0:36:56.27,CDefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}Satō-san, what about\Nif it were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.27,0:36:58.93,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,I'd probably say 'you look adult-like'
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.27,0:36:59.60,DefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(495,778)}'Adult-like'
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.60,0:37:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(585,1018)'}'Adult-like', is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.60,0:37:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,1018)}Like 'you seem like an adult'
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.17,0:37:07.90,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,I don't think that's how it works
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.78,0:37:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,778)}(Osada) That'd make \Nsense if it were a teen
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.21,0:37:13.55,CDefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}So there still more \NEveryone's Theories that I've chosen
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.55,0:37:16.75,CDefaultGreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}Here's the rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.89,0:37:22.89,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,898)}Next is...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.91,0:37:22.92,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,786)}Everyone's Theories\Nas chosen by Kasuga
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.92,0:37:26.69,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,Inffective megaphone theory
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.73,0:37:34.16,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,The megaphone's known for distorting your voice\Nand making it harder for people to understand you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.40,0:37:40.64,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,So for this, we'll have someone known for having a loud voice, Oideyasu Oda, use his real voice
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.74,0:37:46.44,Overlay text,,0,0,0,,And someone known for being quiet, Harusenbon's Haruka, will use a megaphone
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.44,0:37:49.91,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,They'll face the judge, Koga Ken→
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.91,0:37:55.85,COverlay text,,0,0,0,,and we'll investigate which can be heard from farther away
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.85,0:37:58.09,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}The words they'll be shouting
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.09,0:38:00.26,CDefault,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1018)}will be decided by lottery
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.26,0:38:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(255,1018)}(Oda) Shine muscat
